## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This FSD specifies the functional behavior of the Code Indexer Python tool — a standalone CLI script that analyzes source code projects and generates structured metadata for AI agent consumption.

### 1.2 Scope

The Code Indexer accepts a project root path, detects project types, discovers modules, parses source files across 7 languages, and generates 4 output file types. Zero external dependencies (Python stdlib only).

### 1.3 Definitions & Acronyms

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| Signature | A function/class/method declaration line without implementation body |
| Module | A logical grouping of source files (subproject, package, directory with source) |
| KB Payload | JSON object formatted for knowledge base ingestion |
| Project Type | Build system detected from config files (Gradle, Maven, npm, etc.) |

### 1.4 References

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Document | Location |
| BRD | BRD-v1-KSA-7.docx |
| Code Standards | .kiro/steering/code-standards.md |

## 2. System Overview

### 2.1 System Context Diagram

![System Context](data:image/png;base64...)

System Context

The Code Indexer is a standalone CLI tool. It reads source code from the filesystem and writes output files. No network, database, or external service interaction.

**Actors:** - **Developer** — runs the indexer via CLI - **AI Agents** — consume the generated output files

**External Systems:** - **Filesystem** — source code input + output files - **Knowledge Base** — consumes kb-payloads.json (via separate ingestion step)

### 2.2 System Architecture

CLI Input (project path)
 │
 ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Code Indexer Pipeline │
├─────────┬──────────┬─────────┬──────────┤
│ Config │ Detector │ Scanner │ Parser │
│ Loader │ │ │ (7 lang) │
├─────────┴──────────┴─────────┴──────────┤
│ Generator │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
 │
 ▼
Output Files (.analysis/code-intelligence/)

## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Feature: CLI Entry Point

**Source:** BRD Story 1

#### 3.1.1 Description

The indexer is invoked from command line with a project root path. It orchestrates the full pipeline: config → detect → discover → scan → parse → generate.

#### 3.1.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-1 **Actor:** Developer **Preconditions:** Python 3.10+ installed, project directory exists **Postconditions:** Output files generated in .analysis/code-intelligence/

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 | Provides project path |  | python main.py /path/to/project |
| 2 |  | Validates path exists | Checks directory is accessible |
| 3 |  | Loads config | Reads index-config.json or uses defaults |
| 4 |  | Runs pipeline | Detect → Discover → Scan → Parse → Generate |
| 5 |  | Prints summary | Files indexed, modules found, time elapsed |

**Alternative Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| AF-1 | No path provided | Print usage help and exit |
| AF-2 | Config file missing | Use built-in defaults, log info message |

**Exception Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| EF-1 | Path does not exist | Print error “Directory not found: {path}”, exit code 1 |
| EF-2 | Path is a file, not directory | Print error “Expected directory, got file: {path}”, exit code 1 |
| EF-3 | No write permission to output dir | Print error, exit code 1 |

#### 3.1.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-1 | Project path MUST be a valid, accessible directory | BRD Story 1 |
| BR-2 | Output directory is always .analysis/code-intelligence/ relative to project root | BRD Story 1 |
| BR-3 | If output directory doesn’t exist, create it | BRD Story 1 |

### 3.2 Feature: Configuration Loading

**Source:** BRD Story 1, Story 4

#### 3.2.1 Description

The indexer reads configuration from index-config.json in the .analysis/code-intelligence/ directory. If not found, uses sensible defaults.

#### 3.2.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-2 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** Project root path validated **Postconditions:** Configuration loaded into memory

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Checks for config file | Looks for .analysis/code-intelligence/index-config.json |
| 2 |  | Parses JSON | Loads extensions, exclusions, options |
| 3 |  | Merges with defaults | Missing keys filled from defaults |

**Alternative Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| AF-1 | Config file not found | Use all defaults, log “Using default configuration” |
| AF-2 | Config has unknown keys | Ignore unknown keys, use known ones |

**Exception Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| EF-1 | Config file is invalid JSON | Log warning, fall back to defaults |

#### 3.2.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-4 | Default extensions: .kt, .kts, .java, .py, .ts, .tsx, .js, .jsx, .go, .rs | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-5 | Default exclusions: node\_modules, build, dist, .gradle, target, .git, .idea, **pycache** | BRD Appendix |
| BR-6 | Config is optional — tool MUST work without it | BRD Story 4 |

#### 3.2.4 Data Specifications

**Config Schema (index-config.json):**

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
| extensions | string[] | N | [“.kt”,“.java”,“.py”,“.ts”,“.tsx”,“.js”,“.jsx”,“.go”,“.rs”] | File extensions to index |
| exclude\_dirs | string[] | N | [“node\_modules”,“build”,“dist”,“.gradle”,“target”,“.git”,“.idea”,“**pycache**”] | Directories to skip |
| exclude\_patterns | string[] | N | [] | Glob patterns to exclude |
| max\_file\_size\_kb | int | N | 500 | Skip files larger than this |

### 3.3 Feature: Project Type Detection

**Source:** BRD Story 2

#### 3.3.1 Description

Detects project type(s) by scanning for known build/config files in the project root and immediate subdirectories.

#### 3.3.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-3 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** Project root path validated **Postconditions:** List of detected project types returned

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Scans root directory | Lists files in project root |
| 2 |  | Matches build files | Checks against detection rules |
| 3 |  | Scans subdirectories (1 level) | Checks immediate children for build files |
| 4 |  | Returns detected types | List of ProjectType enum values |

**Alternative Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| AF-1 | Multiple types detected | Return all (e.g., [“Gradle”, “npm”]) |
| AF-2 | No build files found | Return [“Unknown”] |

#### 3.3.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-7 | Gradle detected by: build.gradle, build.gradle.kts, settings.gradle.kts | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-8 | Maven detected by: pom.xml | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-9 | npm detected by: package.json | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-10 | Cargo detected by: Cargo.toml | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-11 | Go detected by: go.mod | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-12 | Python detected by: pyproject.toml, setup.py, setup.cfg | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-13 | .NET detected by: *.csproj,* .sln | BRD Story 2 |
| BR-14 | Detection scans root + 1 level deep | BRD Story 2 |

### 3.4 Feature: Module Discovery

**Source:** BRD Story 1

#### 3.4.1 Description

Discovers logical modules within the project based on project type conventions and directory structure.

#### 3.4.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-4 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** Project type(s) detected **Postconditions:** List of modules with paths returned

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Applies discovery strategy | Based on detected project type |
| 2 |  | For Gradle: reads settings.gradle.kts | Extracts include() statements |
| 3 |  | For npm: checks for workspaces | Or treats root as single module |
| 4 |  | For others: scans for src/ directories | Groups by top-level directory |
| 5 |  | Returns module list | Name, path, detected language |

**Alternative Flows:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Condition | Steps |
| AF-1 | Single-module project | Return one module = project root |
| AF-2 | Monorepo with many modules | Return all discovered modules |

#### 3.4.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-15 | Gradle modules from settings.gradle.kts include() | Derived from project type |
| BR-16 | npm modules from package.json workspaces field | Derived from project type |
| BR-17 | Go modules from directories containing .go files | Derived from project type |
| BR-18 | If no modules detected, treat project root as single module | Fallback behavior |

### 3.5 Feature: File Scanning

**Source:** BRD Story 1, Story 3

#### 3.5.1 Description

Scans each module directory recursively for source files matching configured extensions, applying exclusion rules.

#### 3.5.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-5 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** Modules discovered, config loaded **Postconditions:** List of source file paths per module

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Walks directory tree | Recursive traversal of module path |
| 2 |  | Applies exclusion rules | Skip excluded directories |
| 3 |  | Filters by extension | Keep only configured extensions |
| 4 |  | Checks file size | Skip files exceeding max\_file\_size\_kb |
| 5 |  | Returns file list | Sorted list of Path objects |

#### 3.5.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-19 | Skip directories matching exclude\_dirs list | Config |
| BR-20 | Skip files not matching extensions list | Config |
| BR-21 | Skip files larger than max\_file\_size\_kb | Config |
| BR-22 | Skip binary files (detected by null bytes in first 1024 bytes) | BRD Story 1 AC3 |
| BR-23 | Skip files with encoding errors (non-UTF-8) | BRD Story 1 AC4 |

### 3.6 Feature: Source File Parsing

**Source:** BRD Story 3

#### 3.6.1 Description

Parses each source file using regex-based extraction to identify classes, functions, methods, interfaces, and other declarations.

#### 3.6.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-6 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** File list available, file is readable text **Postconditions:** List of signatures extracted from file

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Determines language | From file extension |
| 2 |  | Selects parser | Language-specific regex patterns |
| 3 |  | Reads file content | UTF-8 with error handling |
| 4 |  | Applies regex patterns | Extracts declarations |
| 5 |  | Returns signatures | List of Signature objects |

#### 3.6.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-24 | Kotlin parser extracts: class, object, fun, interface, enum | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-25 | Java parser extracts: class, interface, method, enum | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-26 | Python parser extracts: class, def, async def, decorators | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-27 | TypeScript parser extracts: class, function, interface, type, const arrow | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-28 | JavaScript parser extracts: class, function, const arrow, export | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-29 | Go parser extracts: struct, interface, func, method (receiver) | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-30 | Rust parser extracts: struct, enum, trait, impl, fn | BRD Story 3 |
| BR-31 | Parser MUST handle multi-line signatures | BRD Story 3 AC2 |
| BR-32 | Parser SHOULD ignore declarations inside comments | BRD Story 3 AC3 |

#### 3.6.4 Data Specifications

**Signature Output:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Description |
| name | string | Declaration name (e.g., “MyClass”, “processData”) |
| kind | enum | class / function / interface / enum / struct / trait / impl / method |
| visibility | string | public / private / internal / protected / package (if detectable) |
| line | int | Line number where declaration starts |
| params | string | Parameter list as raw string (if function/method) |
| decorators | string[] | Decorators/annotations (Python, Java, Kotlin) |

### 3.7 Feature: Output Generation

**Source:** BRD Story 1, Story 6

#### 3.7.1 Description

Generates 4 types of output files from the parsed data.

#### 3.7.2 Use Case

**Use Case ID:** UC-7 **Actor:** System (internal) **Preconditions:** All modules parsed, signatures extracted **Postconditions:** Output files written to .analysis/code-intelligence/

**Main Flow:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Actor | System | Description |
| 1 |  | Generates project-structure.md | Overview with project type, modules, stats |
| 2 |  | Generates modules/\*.md | One file per module with signatures |
| 3 |  | Generates index-metadata.json | File-level metadata with hashes |
| 4 |  | Generates kb-payloads.json | KB-ready documents per module |
| 5 |  | Prints summary | Total files, modules, time |

#### 3.7.3 Business Rules

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Rule ID | Rule | Source |
| BR-33 | project-structure.md includes: project name, type, tech stack, module list, stats | BRD Story 1 |
| BR-34 | modules/{name}.md includes: module purpose, file list, key signatures | BRD Story 1 |
| BR-35 | index-metadata.json includes: per-file hash, line count, signature count | BRD Story 1 |
| BR-36 | kb-payloads.json is array of {title, content, tags} objects | BRD Story 6 |
| BR-37 | One KB payload per module | BRD Story 6 |
| BR-38 | Output directory created if not exists | BR-3 |

#### 3.7.4 Data Specifications

**index-metadata.json schema:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Description |
| project\_name | string | Detected project name |
| project\_types | string[] | Detected project types |
| indexed\_at | string | ISO 8601 timestamp |
| total\_files | int | Number of files indexed |
| total\_modules | int | Number of modules discovered |
| files | object[] | Per-file metadata array |
| files[].path | string | Relative path from project root |
| files[].hash | string | SHA-256 content hash |
| files[].lines | int | Total line count |
| files[].signatures | int | Number of signatures extracted |
| files[].language | string | Detected language |
| files[].module | string | Module this file belongs to |

**kb-payloads.json schema:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Field | Type | Description |
| title | string | “Code Index — {module\_name}” |
| content | string | Module summary with key signatures |
| tags | string | “code-index, {module\_name}, {language}” |

## 4. Data Model

### 4.1 Internal Data Structures

This is a CLI tool with no persistent storage. All data is in-memory during execution.

#### Entity: Config

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Attribute | Type | Required | Description |
| extensions | list[str] | Y | File extensions to include |
| exclude\_dirs | list[str] | Y | Directories to skip |
| exclude\_patterns | list[str] | N | Glob patterns to exclude |
| max\_file\_size\_kb | int | Y | Max file size threshold |

#### Entity: ProjectInfo

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Attribute | Type | Required | Description |
| name | str | Y | Project name (from directory name) |
| root\_path | Path | Y | Absolute path to project root |
| types | list[str] | Y | Detected project types |
| modules | list[Module] | Y | Discovered modules |

#### Entity: Module

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Attribute | Type | Required | Description |
| name | str | Y | Module name |
| path | Path | Y | Absolute path to module root |
| language | str | Y | Primary language |
| files | list[SourceFile] | Y | Source files in this module |

#### Entity: SourceFile

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Attribute | Type | Required | Description |
| path | Path | Y | Absolute file path |
| relative\_path | str | Y | Path relative to project root |
| language | str | Y | Detected language from extension |
| lines | int | Y | Total line count |
| hash | str | Y | SHA-256 content hash |
| signatures | list[Signature] | Y | Extracted signatures |

#### Entity: Signature

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Attribute | Type | Required | Description |
| name | str | Y | Declaration name |
| kind | str | Y | class/function/interface/enum/struct/trait/impl/method |
| visibility | str | N | public/private/internal/protected |
| line | int | Y | Line number |
| params | str | N | Parameter string |
| decorators | list[str] | N | Annotations/decorators |

