| Direction | Outbound (generate file for later ingestion) |
| Data Format | JSON array |
| Frequency | After each indexing run |

## 6. Processing Logic

### 6.1 Main Pipeline

**Trigger:** CLI invocation with project path **Input:** Project root directory path **Output:** 4 output file types

**Processing Steps:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Description | Error Handling |
| 1 | Validate CLI args | Exit with usage help if invalid |
| 2 | Load config | Fall back to defaults on error |
| 3 | Detect project types | Return “Unknown” if none detected |
| 4 | Discover modules | Use root as single module if none found |
| 5 | Scan files per module | Skip unreadable files, log warning |
| 6 | Parse each file | Skip unparseable files, log warning |
| 7 | Generate outputs | Write all 4 output types |
| 8 | Print summary | Always print, even on partial failure |

### 6.2 File Parsing Pipeline (per file)

**Trigger:** File found during scan **Input:** File path **Output:** List of Signature objects

**Pseudocode:**

def parse\_file(path: Path) -> list[Signature]:
 content = read\_utf8(path) # skip if encoding error
 if is\_binary(content):
 return []

 language = detect\_language(path.suffix)
 parser = get\_parser(language) # select regex patterns

 signatures = []
 for pattern in parser.patterns:
 for match in pattern.finditer(content):
 sig = extract\_signature(match, language)
 signatures.append(sig)

 return signatures

### 6.3 Project Type Detection Logic

**Pseudocode:**

def detect\_types(root: Path) -> list[str]:
 types = []
 files = list\_files(root) # root level only

 if any(f in files for f in ["build.gradle", "build.gradle.kts", "settings.gradle.kts"]):
 types.append("Gradle")
 if "pom.xml" in files:
 types.append("Maven")
 if "package.json" in files:
 types.append("npm")
 if "Cargo.toml" in files:
 types.append("Cargo")
 if "go.mod" in files:
 types.append("Go")
 if any(f in files for f in ["pyproject.toml", "setup.py", "setup.cfg"]):
 types.append("Python")
 if any(f.endswith((".csproj", ".sln")) for f in files):
 types.append(".NET")

 # Also check 1 level deep for monorepos
 for subdir in list\_dirs(root):
 sub\_types = detect\_types\_shallow(subdir)
 types.extend(sub\_types)

 return list(set(types)) or ["Unknown"]

## 7. Security Requirements

### 7.1 Authentication & Authorization

Not applicable — standalone CLI tool with no authentication.

### 7.2 Data Sensitivity

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Data Type | Classification | Requirement |
| Source code (input) | Internal | Read-only access, never modified |
| Output files | Internal | Written to project directory only |
| File hashes | Public | SHA-256, no sensitive data |

### 7.3 Security Constraints

* Tool MUST NOT modify source files
* Tool MUST NOT send data over network
* Tool MUST NOT execute any code from parsed files
* Output MUST NOT contain file contents (only signatures/metadata)

## 8. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
| Performance | Fast indexing | 100 files < 5s, 1000 files < 30s |
| Portability | Cross-platform | Works on Windows, macOS, Linux |
| Maintainability | Small files | All .py files ≤ 200 lines |
| Maintainability | Small functions | All functions ≤ 20 lines |
| Reliability | Graceful errors | Never crashes, always prints summary |
| Compatibility | Python stdlib only | Zero pip dependencies |
| Compatibility | Python version | 3.10+ (for match statements, type hints) |

## 9. Error Handling

### 9.1 Error Scenarios

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Scenario | Severity | User Message | Expected Behavior |
| Invalid path | Critical | “Error: Directory not found: {path}” | Exit code 1 |
| No write permission | Critical | “Error: Cannot write to output directory” | Exit code 1 |
| Binary file encountered | Info | (logged only) | Skip file, continue |
| Encoding error | Warning | “Warning: Skipping {file} (encoding error)” | Skip file, continue |
| Parse error in file | Warning | “Warning: Could not parse {file}” | Skip file, continue |
| Empty project (no source files) | Warning | “Warning: No source files found” | Generate empty outputs |
| Config parse error | Warning | “Warning: Invalid config, using defaults” | Use defaults, continue |

### 9.2 Exit Codes

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Code | Meaning |
| 0 | Success (even with warnings) |
| 1 | Fatal error (invalid path, no permissions) |
| 2 | Invalid arguments |

## 10. Testing Considerations

### 10.1 Test Scenarios

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Scenario | Input | Expected Output | Priority |
| TC-1 | Index Kotlin/Gradle project | MCPOrchestration project | All 4 output files generated | High |
| TC-2 | Index Python project | Code indexer itself | Correct self-indexing | High |
| TC-3 | Detect Gradle type | Project with build.gradle.kts | types = [“Gradle”] | High |
| TC-4 | Detect multiple types | Project with build.gradle.kts + package.json | types = [“Gradle”, “npm”] | High |
| TC-5 | Handle empty directory | Empty dir | types = [“Unknown”], empty outputs | Medium |
| TC-6 | Handle binary files | Dir with .exe + .py files | Only .py files indexed | Medium |
| TC-7 | Parse Kotlin signatures | .kt file with classes/functions | All declarations extracted | High |
| TC-8 | Parse Python signatures | .py file with classes/functions | All declarations extracted | High |
| TC-9 | Config override | Custom index-config.json | Respects custom extensions | Medium |
| TC-10 | Large project performance | 1000+ files | Completes < 30s | Medium |

## 11. Appendix

### File Organization (from Code Standards)

code-indexer/
├── main.py ← Entry point, CLI arg parsing, pipeline orchestration
├── config.py ← Configuration loading and defaults
├── detector.py ← Project type detection
├── discovery.py ← Module discovery
├── scanner.py ← File scanning + filtering
├── parser.py ← Parser dispatcher (routes to language parsers)
├── parsers/
│ ├── \_\_init\_\_.py
│ ├── kotlin.py ← Kotlin regex patterns
│ ├── java.py ← Java regex patterns
│ ├── python.py ← Python regex patterns
│ ├── typescript.py ← TypeScript regex patterns
│ ├── javascript.py ← JavaScript regex patterns
│ ├── go.py ← Go regex patterns
│ └── rust.py ← Rust regex patterns
├── generator.py ← Output file generation
├── models.py ← Data classes (Config, Module, Signature, etc.)
└── utils.py ← Shared utilities (hash, path helpers, file I/O)

### API Contract (CLI Interface)

**Command:**

python main.py <project-root> [--config <path>] [--verbose] [--output <dir>]

**Arguments:**

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Argument | Required | Default | Description |
| project-root | Yes | — | Path to project directory |
| –config | No | auto-detect | Path to index-config.json |
| –verbose | No | false | Print detailed progress |
| –output | No | .analysis/code-intelligence/ | Output directory (relative to project root) |

**Output (stdout):**

Code Indexer — Python v1.0
Project: MCPOrchestration
Types: Gradle, npm
Modules: 7
Files indexed: 342
Signatures: 1,205
Time: 4.2s
Output: .analysis/code-intelligence/

